article.headline: Radford 81, Brevard (NC) 53
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- R.J. Price scored 20 points and Jalen Carethers had career highs with 12 points and seven rebounds to help Radford beat Brevard 81-53 Wednesday. Manzey Miller added 11 points and three assists for Radford (3-3), which is one of the youngest teams in the country, with one senior and one junior on a 14-man roster. Dominique Pickett scored 18 points, and Miles Leathers added 16 points for the Division II Tornadoes (0-4), who turned the ball over 25 times.
